## Claude-specific

- Use `/research` for deep documentation/library lookups when guessing at an
  API surface would be wrong.
- Skills (in `~/.claude/skills/`) are the right place for repeatable workflows.
- Delegate independent, bounded work without asking: read-heavy exploration,
  primary-source research, log analysis, test runs, and adversarial review.
  Keep overlapping edits in one agent and collect every result before handing
  work back.
- Treat `packages/agent-skills.txt` as the installed-skill registry. Audit it
  with `install/skills-sync.sh check`; `npx skills check` mutates the tree.
